dct_title_s: Plan of the city of Washington in the territory of Columbia : ceded by the states of Virginia and Maryland to the United States of America, and by them established as the seat of their government, after the year MDCCC
dct_description_sm: Shows block numbers and proposed government buildings.  Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings.  Also covers Georgetown.  Watermark: [crown over fleur-de-lis].  Includes text, notes, and coat-of-arms.
dcat_keyword_sm: Georgetown (Washington, d.c.) Maps Early Works to 1800
